{
  "info": {
    "name": "Tahadaw - Gift Card Flow (full: create user + premium + AI message + card)",
    "description": "Full end-to-end test for Flow 13 (Premium Gift Card) starting from nothing:\ncreate a user, pay for premium via Moyasar sandbox (with the one-time 3-D Secure approval),\ncreate a recipient + gift plan, generate AI gift recommendations and pick one, generate an\nAI gift MESSAGE, then build the branded gift card (navy #2D3A47 design + Tahadaw logo + QR)\nusing that generated message, view the rendered PNG, and (re)send it by email.\n\nThe gift card link uses a YouTube URL ({{youtubeUrl}}) which is encoded into the QR on the card.\n\nIMPORTANT — the premium payment needs ONE manual browser step (this is how real card payments work):\n  Step 3 (Pay Premium) returns a 3-D Secure URL. Moyasar sandbox does NOT auto-approve.\n  1. Run step 3. The test tab / console prints a '3DS_URL'.\n  2. Open that URL in a browser and click the green 'Complete / Pay' (sandbox) button to approve.\n  3. Run step 4 (Refresh Payment Status) -> it becomes PAID and premium is activated.\n  4. Continue with the rest.\n\nIf you would rather skip payment entirely, load seed-part3.sql (premium user id=3),\nset {{userId}} = 3 manually, and run from step 5 onward (note: the seeded plan uses a recipient\nowned by user 1, so still create your own recipient + plan via steps 6-8).\n\nNOTE: creating the card (step 12) AUTO-SENDS it to the owner's email. Step 16 just re-sends it.\nSet {{cardEmail}} (and ideally use a real email when creating the user) to actually receive it.\n\nConfig needed in application-local.properties: openai.api.key, moyasar.api.key (sk_test_...),\nand working spring.mail.* (Gmail App Password) for the email steps.\n\nRun the steps top-to-bottom. Each step stores the IDs it creates into collection variables.\n\nFlow:\n1. Create User\n2. Find User Id              (capture {{userId}})\n3. Pay Premium (Moyasar)     (capture {{moyasarPaymentId}}, prints 3DS_URL)\n   --- approve the 3DS URL in a browser ---\n4. Refresh Payment Status    (-> PAID, activates premium)\n5. Check Premium Status      (guard)\n6. Add Recipient\n7. Find Recipient Id         (capture {{recipientId}})\n8. Create Gift Plan          (capture {{giftPlanId}})\n9. Generate Gift Recommendations (AI)  (capture {{recommendationId}})\n10. Select Recommendation\n11. Generate Gift Message (AI)         (capture {{giftMessageId}})\n12. Create Gift Card (uses {{giftMessageId}} + YouTube link)  (capture {{giftCardId}})\n13. View Gift Card Image (PNG)\n14. Get Gift Card Metadata\n15. List My Gift Cards\n16. Re-send Gift Card Email\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "username", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "email", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "userId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "moyasarPaymentId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "recipientName", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "recipientId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "giftPlanId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "recommendationId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "giftMessageId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "giftCardId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "cardEmail", "value": "recipient@example.com", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "youtubeUrl", "value": "https://youtu.be/BeUwc7L1Rug?si=qJkAbEBdSM4a7IVg", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Create User",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// Unique username/email so re-runs don't hit unique constraints.",
              "const stamp = Date.now().toString().slice(-7);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('username', 'carduser' + stamp);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('email', 'carduser' + stamp + '@example.com');"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('User created (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users/add", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "users", "add"] },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{username}}\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\",\n  \"fullName\": \"Card Tester\",\n  \"email\": \"{{email}}\",\n  \"phoneNumber\": \"0512345678\"\n}"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Find User Id",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const users = pm.response.json();",
              "const wanted = pm.collectionVariables.get('username');",
              "const me = (Array.isArray(users) ? users : []).find(u => u.username === wanted);",
              "pm.test('Found created user', () => pm.expect(me, 'user with username ' + wanted).to.be.an('object'));",
              "if (me) { pm.collectionVariables.set('userId', me.id); console.log('userId =', me.id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users/get", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "users", "get"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Pay Premium (Moyasar sandbox)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Payment created (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const p = pm.response.json();",
              "if (p && p.transactionId) { pm.collectionVariables.set('moyasarPaymentId', p.transactionId); }",
              "console.log('moyasarStatus =', p.moyasarStatus, '| local status =', p.status);",
              "if (p.moyasarStatus === 'paid') {",
              "  console.log('Already PAID — premium activated. Skip step 4, go to step 5.');",
              "} else if (p.transactionUrl) {",
              "  console.log('================ 3DS_URL (open in browser, approve, then run step 4) ================');",
              "  console.log(p.transactionUrl);",
              "  console.log('====================================================================================');",
              "} else {",
              "  console.warn('No transaction_url returned. Check Moyasar key / response:', JSON.stringify(p));",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Has Moyasar payment id', () => pm.expect(p.transactionId, 'transactionId').to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/payments/premium",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "payments", "premium"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"userId\": {{userId}},\n  \"name\": \"Premium Tester\",\n  \"number\": \"4111111111111111\",\n  \"cvc\": \"123\",\n  \"month\": \"12\",\n  \"year\": \"2030\",\n  \"callbackUrl\": \"{{base_url}}/api/v1/payments/webhook/moyasar\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Creates a Moyasar sandbox card payment for premium. Uses the standard test card 4111 1111 1111 1111. Returns a 3-D Secure transactionUrl (printed in the Console / Test results). Open it in a browser and approve, then run step 4."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Refresh Payment Status (after 3DS approval)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Refresh ok (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const p = pm.response.json();",
              "console.log('moyasarStatus =', p.moyasarStatus, '| local status =', p.status);",
              "if (p.status !== 'PAID') {",
              "  console.warn('Not PAID yet. Open the 3DS_URL from step 3 in a browser, approve it, then run this step again.');",
              "}",
              "pm.test('Payment is PAID (premium activated)', () => pm.expect(p.status).to.eql('PAID'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/payments/moyasar-status/{{moyasarPaymentId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "payments", "moyasar-status", "{{moyasarPaymentId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Pulls the latest status from Moyasar for the payment created in step 3. After you approve the 3DS page, this turns the payment PAID and activates premium for the user."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Check Premium Status (guard)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status call ok (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "let body = {};",
              "try { body = pm.response.json(); } catch (e) {}",
              "const isPremium = body.premium === true || body.isPremium === true;",
              "if (!isPremium) {",
              "  console.warn('User is NOT premium yet. Complete steps 3 + 4 (3DS approval) first.');",
              "}",
              "pm.test('User is premium (required for gift cards)', () => pm.expect(isPremium, 'isPremium').to.eql(true));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/premium/status?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "premium", "status"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Add Recipient",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const stamp = Date.now().toString().slice(-7);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('recipientName', 'CardRecipient ' + stamp);"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Recipient added (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/recipients/add/{{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "recipients", "add", "{{userId}}"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"{{recipientName}}\",\n  \"relationship\": \"sister\",\n  \"age\": 24,\n  \"gender\": \"female\",\n  \"interests\": \"reading, coffee, travel\",\n  \"hobbies\": \"photography\",\n  \"favoriteColors\": \"green, beige\",\n  \"personalityStyle\": \"thoughtful\",\n  \"consentAcknowledged\": true\n}"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Find Recipient Id",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const recipients = pm.response.json();",
              "const wanted = pm.collectionVariables.get('recipientName');",
              "const list = Array.isArray(recipients) ? recipients : [];",
              "const mine = list.filter(r => r.name === wanted);",
              "const r = mine.length ? mine[mine.length - 1] : null;",
              "pm.test('Found created recipient', () => pm.expect(r, 'recipient named ' + wanted).to.be.an('object'));",
              "if (r) { pm.collectionVariables.set('recipientId', r.id); console.log('recipientId =', r.id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/recipients/get", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "recipients", "get"] }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "8. Create Gift Plan",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Gift plan created (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const plan = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Plan has id', () => pm.expect(plan).to.have.property('id'));",
              "if (plan && plan.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('giftPlanId', plan.id); console.log('giftPlanId =', plan.id); }"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-plans?userId={{userId}}&recipientId={{recipientId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-plans"],
          "query": [
            { "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" },
            { "key": "recipientId", "value": "{{recipientId}}" }
          ]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"occasionType\": \"GRADUATION\",\n  \"occasionDate\": \"2026-07-01\",\n  \"budgetMinor\": 30000,\n  \"currency\": \"SAR\",\n  \"preferredGiftStyle\": \"PRACTICAL\",\n  \"language\": \"ar\"\n}"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "9. Generate Gift Recommendations (AI)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Recommendations generated (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const recs = pm.response.json();",
              "const list = Array.isArray(recs) ? recs : [];",
              "pm.test('At least one recommendation returned', () => pm.expect(list.length).to.be.above(0));",
              "if (list.length) {",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('recommendationId', list[0].id);",
              "  console.log('recommendationId =', list[0].id, '| name =', list[0].productName);",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-plans/get-rec/{{userId}}/{{giftPlanId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-plans", "get-rec", "{{userId}}", "{{giftPlanId}}"]
        },
        "description": "AI-generates 3-5 gift ideas from the recipient + occasion context. No questions chain required."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "10. Select Recommendation",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Recommendation selected (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "PUT",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-plans/select-Recomendation/{{userId}}/{{recommendationId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-plans", "select-Recomendation", "{{userId}}", "{{recommendationId}}"]
        },
        "description": "Marks one AI gift idea as selected. Required before a gift MESSAGE can be generated."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "11. Generate Gift Message (AI)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Message generated (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const m = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Message has id', () => pm.expect(m).to.have.property('id'));",
              "if (m && m.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('giftMessageId', m.id); }",
              "console.log('giftMessageId =', m.id);",
              "console.log('messageText =', m.messageText);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-plans/{{giftPlanId}}/messages/generate?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-plans", "{{giftPlanId}}", "messages", "generate"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"tone\": \"warm\",\n  \"language\": \"ar\",\n  \"dialect\": \"\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "AI-generates a heartfelt Arabic gift message tied to the selected idea. Its id is fed into the gift card so the card shows THIS message instead of the default."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "12. Create Gift Card (uses generated message + YouTube link)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Gift card created (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const card = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Card has id', () => pm.expect(card).to.have.property('id'));",
              "if (card && card.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('giftCardId', card.id); console.log('giftCardId =', card.id); }",
              "pm.test('Uses generated message', () => pm.expect(String(card.giftMessageId)).to.eql(String(pm.collectionVariables.get('giftMessageId'))));",
              "pm.test('Link URL stored', () => pm.expect(card.linkUrl).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('youtubeUrl')));",
              "console.log('card status =', card.status, '(SENT means auto-email succeeded)');"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-plans/{{giftPlanId}}/gift-card?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-plans", "{{giftPlanId}}", "gift-card"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"giftMessageId\": {{giftMessageId}},\n  \"cardSize\": \"MEDIUM\",\n  \"linkType\": \"VIDEO\",\n  \"linkUrl\": \"{{youtubeUrl}}\",\n  \"sentToEmail\": \"{{cardEmail}}\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Builds the card using the AI-generated message (giftMessageId). Auto-sends to sentToEmail/owner. To use the default message instead, remove the giftMessageId line."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "13. View Gift Card Image (PNG)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Image returned (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "pm.test('Content-Type is PNG', () => pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('image/png'));",
              "pm.test('Image has bytes', () => pm.expect(pm.response.responseSize).to.be.above(1000));",
              "console.log('Open this URL in a browser to SEE the card:');",
              "console.log(pm.variables.replaceIn('{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-cards/{{giftCardId}}/image?userId={{userId}}'));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-cards/{{giftCardId}}/image?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-cards", "{{giftCardId}}", "image"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "14. Get Gift Card Metadata",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Metadata ok (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const card = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Matches created card', () => pm.expect(String(card.id)).to.eql(String(pm.collectionVariables.get('giftCardId'))));",
              "console.log('status =', card.status, '| linkType =', card.linkType);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-cards/{{giftCardId}}?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-cards", "{{giftCardId}}"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "15. List My Gift Cards",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('List ok (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const list = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Contains the created card', () => pm.expect((Array.isArray(list) ? list : []).some(c => String(c.id) === String(pm.collectionVariables.get('giftCardId')))).to.eql(true));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-cards/my?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-cards", "my"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "16. Re-send Gift Card Email",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "pm.test('Email sent (200)', () => pm.response.code === 200);",
              "const card = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('Status is SENT', () => pm.expect(card.status).to.eql('SENT'));",
              "console.log('Sent to:', card.sentToEmail);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/gift-cards/{{giftCardId}}/send-email?userId={{userId}}",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "gift-cards", "{{giftCardId}}", "send-email"],
          "query": [{ "key": "userId", "value": "{{userId}}" }]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{cardEmail}}\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Step 12 already auto-sends the card. This re-sends it (e.g. to a different address)."
      }
    }
  ]
}
